            <h2 style="font-size: 1.875rem; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary-color);">Limited Lifetime Warranty</h2>
            
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">All Dean Aaron Jewels come with a limited lifetime warranty against manufacturing defects. This warranty covers:</p>
            
            <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Manufacturing Defects:</strong> Any flaws in materials or workmanship that affect the structural integrity or functionality of the piece.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Prong Repairs:</strong> Repair or replacement of prongs that secure gemstones, if they become worn or damaged under normal wear.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Stone Tightening:</strong> Resetting of loose stones that were originally set by Dean Aaron Jewels.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Rhodium Plating:</strong> One complimentary rhodium plating per year for white gold pieces (additional platings available at a nominal fee).</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Ring Sizing:</strong> One complimentary ring sizing within the first year of purchase (additional sizings available at a nominal fee).</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p style="line-height: 1.6;">To maintain your warranty coverage, we recommend having your jewelry inspected and professionally cleaned at a Dean Aaron Jewels location at least once a year.</p>
        </div>
        
        <div style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
            <h2 style="font-size: 1.875rem; font-weight: bold; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; color: var(--primary-color);">What's Not Covered</h2>
            
            <p style="line-height: 1.6; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Our warranty does not cover:</p>
            
            <ul style="list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Normal Wear and Tear:</strong> Natural wearing of metal over time with regular use.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Accidental Damage:</strong> Damage caused by impacts, crushing, or other accidents.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Loss or Theft:</strong> Missing jewelry or stolen items.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Improper Care:</strong> Damage resulting from exposure to chemicals, improper cleaning, or failure to follow our care instructions.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Third-Party Modifications:</strong> Any alterations, repairs, or resizing performed by jewelers other than Dean Aaron Jewels.</li>
                <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;"><strong>Natural Characteristics of Gemstones:</strong> Inclusions or other natural features that are present at the time of purchase.</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p style="line-height: 1.6;">While these situations are not covered under our warranty, we do offer repair services at reasonable rates for these types of issues.</p>
